defs.docs: Fork of Arc for Servo. This has the following advantages over std::sync::Arc:

defs.name: NonZeroPtrMut
defs.docs:
Wrapper type for pointers to get the non-zero optimization. When
 NonZero/Shared/Unique are stabilized, we should just use Shared
 here to get the same effect. Gankro is working on this in [1].

defs.name: UniqueArc
defs.docs: An Arc that is known to be uniquely owned

defs.docs: Construct a new UniqueArc

defs.name: with_raw_offset_arc
defs.docs:
Temporarily converts |self| into a bonafide RawOffsetArc and exposes it to the
 provided callback. The refcount is not modified.

defs.name: heap_ptr
defs.docs:
Returns the address on the heap of the Arc itself -- not the T within it -- for memory
 reporting.

defs.name: HeaderSlice
defs.docs:
Structure to allow Arc-managing some fixed-sized data and a variably-sized
 slice in a single allocation.

defs.name: header
defs.docs: The fixed-sized data.

defs.name: slice
defs.docs: The dynamically-sized data.

defs.name: from_header_and_iter
defs.value: fn <I> (header: H, mut items: I) -> Self
defs.docs:
Creates an Arc for a HeaderSlice using the given header struct and
 iterator to generate the slice. The resulting Arc will be fat.

defs.name: HeaderWithLength
defs.docs:
Header data with an inline length. Consumers that use HeaderWithLength as the
 Header type in HeaderSlice can take advantage of ThinArc.

defs.name: header
defs.docs: The fixed-sized data.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new HeaderWithLength.

defs.name: with_arc
defs.docs:
Temporarily converts |self| into a bonafide Arc and exposes it to the
 provided callback. The refcount is not modified.

defs.name: heap_ptr
defs.docs:
Returns the address on the heap of the ThinArc itself -- not the T
 within it -- for memory reporting.

defs.name: into_thin
defs.docs:
Converts an Arc into a ThinArc. This consumes the Arc, so the refcount
 is not modified.

defs.name: from_thin
defs.docs:
Converts a ThinArc into an Arc. This consumes the ThinArc, so the refcount
 is not modified.

defs.name: RawOffsetArc
defs.docs:
An Arc, except it holds a pointer to the T instead of to the
 entire ArcInner.

defs.name: with_arc
defs.docs:
Temporarily converts |self| into a bonafide Arc and exposes it to the
 provided callback. The refcount is not modified.

defs.name: make_mut
defs.docs:
If uniquely owned, provide a mutable reference
 Else create a copy, and mutate that

defs.name: clone_arc
defs.docs: Clone it as an Arc

defs.name: borrow_arc
defs.docs:
Produce a pointer to the data that can be converted back
 to an arc

defs.name: into_raw_offset
defs.docs:
Converts an Arc into a RawOffsetArc. This consumes the Arc, so the refcount
 is not modified.

defs.name: from_raw_offset
defs.docs:
Converts a RawOffsetArc into an Arc. This consumes the RawOffsetArc, so the refcount
 is not modified.

defs.name: ArcBorrow
defs.docs:
A "borrowed Arc". This is a pointer to
 a T that is known to have been allocated within an
 Arc.

defs.name: from_ref
defs.docs:
For constructing from a reference known to be Arc-backed,
 e.g. if we obtain such a reference over FFI
